            "id": "519ac87dc6234717af7a3",
            "questionText": "Given that the planetary nebula is observed at a distance of $!$9.5 \\times 10^{15} \\text{ m}$!$, compute its distance in light-years. Use the conversion factor that $!$1 \\text{ light-year} = 9.461 \\times 10^{15} \\text{ m}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "fa5336436600470596012",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct conversion approach. Which expression correctly represents the conversion from a distance in meters to light-years?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "97e4ba3a-38d3-43c2-99e7-b74649b32c41"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Distance in ly} = \\frac{\\text{Distance in m}}{9.461 \\times 10^{15}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Distance in ly} = \\text{Distance in m} \\times 9.461 \\times 10^{15}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Distance in ly} = \\text{Distance in m} - 9.461 \\times 10^{15}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cb197c84a3aa48179a107",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now, use the conversion by dividing the given distance $!$9.5 \\times 10^{15}\\text{ m}$!$ by $!$9.461 \\times 10^{15}\\text{ m}$!$. Compute the resulting numerical value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1.0041"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "light-years",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "97e4ba3a-38d3-43c2-99e7-b74649b32c41"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "ed026941198a49ee90085",
                    "stepText": "Excellent work. Now round your computed value to a reasonable level of precision (to the nearest whole number) to express the distance in light-years.",
                    "stepText2": "",
